<subSubSection id="C36B657AFFA95D2FC4C3FB685321B3D1" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCE36F1FFA95D2FC4C3FB6851FBB3FE" blockId="2.[151,1438,1231,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="B905EAE3FFA95D2FC4C3FB685004B293" bold="true" box="[151,283,1231,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C714D72FFA95D2FC577FB775386B293" box="[291,665,1232,1257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Actenosigynes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cornales" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mantiqueirensis">
<emphasis id="B905EAE3FFA95D2FC577FB775386B293" box="[291,665,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Actenosigynes mantiqueirensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily distinguished from the only other species in the genus by its entirely black-pubescent mesosoma (
<figureCitation id="134A2A74FFA95D2FC68AFB51523AB36A" box="[734,805,1270,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,215,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[260,1327,194,1953]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Female of Actenosigynes mantiqueirensis sp. nov., holotype— a) habitus, dorsal view; b) head, frontal view; c) metasoma, ventral view (notice the shiny integument of sternal discs); d) habitus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB924D6FFA95D2FC741FB51523AB36A" box="[789,805,1270,1296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a,d) (ferruginous dorsally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D72FFA95D2FC020FB505412B36A" box="[1140,1293,1271,1296]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Actenosigynes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cornales" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulvoniger">
<emphasis id="B905EAE3FFA95D2FC020FB505412B36A" box="[1140,1293,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">A. fulvoniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<figureCitation id="134A2A74FFA95D2FC179FB515473B36A" box="[1325,1388,1270,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,195,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[181,1403,195,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Female of Actenosigynes fulvoniger (Michener, 1989) — a) habitus, dorsal view; b) head, frontal view; c) metasoma, ventral view (notice the dull integument of sternal discs); d) habitus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191458/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB924D6FFA95D2FC135FB515473B36A" box="[1377,1388,1270,1296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
a,d) and by the light-yellow pilosity on the terga (
<figureCitation id="134A2A74FFA95D2FC694FABA5215B34D" box="[704,778,1309,1335]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[263,1326,215,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[260,1327,194,1953]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Female of Actenosigynes mantiqueirensis sp. nov., holotype— a) habitus, dorsal view; b) head, frontal view; c) metasoma, ventral view (notice the shiny integument of sternal discs); d) habitus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB924D6FFA95D2FC6AEFABA5215B34D" box="[762,778,1309,1335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a,d) (entirely black in 
<emphasis id="B905EAE3FFA95D2FC04CFABA55CDB34C" box="[1048,1234,1309,1334]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">A. fulvoniger—</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="134A2A74FFA95D2FC086FABA540AB34D" box="[1234,1301,1309,1335]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,256,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[181,1402,195,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[181,1403,195,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Female of Actenosigynes fulvoniger (Michener, 1989) — a) habitus, dorsal view; b) head, frontal view; c) metasoma, ventral view (notice the dull integument of sternal discs); d) habitus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191458/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number id="3DB924D6FFA95D2FC15EFABA540AB34D" box="[1290,1301,1309,1335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
a,d). Other characters distinguishing these species are given in the identification key and (in italics) in the description, below.
</paragraph>
